    <h1>Help</h1>

    <h2>C:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>An old but extremely fast programming language, mainly used in operating systems and embedded systems development.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>It gives you deep understanding of how computers work — memory management, low-level operations, and system processes.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Create operating systems, device drivers, embedded software, and performance-critical applications.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>CPP:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>An extension of C that adds support for object-oriented programming. It’s widely used in games, desktop applications, and high-performance software.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>It's a powerful and flexible language that opens doors to game development, simulations, and finance-related software.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Build video games, real-time simulators, desktop software, and complex systems.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>CS:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A language developed by Microsoft, commonly used for Windows apps, games (with Unity), and web development using .NET.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Modern, beginner-friendly, and highly in demand. Great for desktop software and game development.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Create Windows applications, Unity games, web backends, and enterprise tools.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>GO:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A fast, efficient, and simple language created by Google, ideal for backend services and cloud-native development.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Easy to learn, highly performant, and great for scalable systems and microservices.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Build APIs, backend servers, tools for cloud infrastructure, and microservices.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>JAVA:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A versatile programming language used in Android apps, backend servers, and enterprise applications.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Highly popular and demanded in the job market. Provides a strong foundation for large-scale software development.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Develop Android apps, enterprise systems, web backends, and cross-platform applications.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>PYTHON:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>An easy-to-learn language used in web development, data science, artificial intelligence, and automation.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Highly versatile, beginner-friendly, and supported by a large community. Ideal for rapid development and learning.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Create web apps, automate tasks, build AI models, and analyze data.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>HTML:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A markup language used to create the structure of web pages.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Essential for any web developer, as it defines the content and layout of websites.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Create the skeleton of any website, from basic pages to complex web applications.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>CSS:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A styling language used to control the appearance and design of web pages.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Allows you to make attractive, responsive, and user-friendly websites.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Style websites with colors, layouts, fonts, animations, and responsive design.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>JS:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A programming language used to add interactivity and dynamic behavior to websites.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>The core language of modern web development, essential for frontend and increasingly used on the backend.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Build dynamic websites, web applications, mobile apps, and interactive user interfaces.</code>
    </h3>

    <h2>PHP:</h2>
    <h3>
        What it is: <code>A server-side programming language used to create dynamic websites and web applications.</code><br>
        Why learn it: <code>Still widely used in web development, especially with MySQL databases and platforms like WordPress.</code><br>
        What can you do with it: <code>Build websites, CMS platforms, e-commerce stores, and backend services.</code>
    </h3>
